<TITLE> Boucher reclaims test wicketkeeping record </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DHAKA, Feb 24 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - South Africa's Mark Boucher reclaimed the world record for the most test dismissals by a wicketkeeper during the first test against Bangladesh on Sunday. Boucher captured his 417th victim, breaking the previous record of 416 held briefly by Australian Adam Gilchrist, when he caught Bangladesh batsmen Mushfiqur Rahim for two off the bowling of Jaques Kallis. Boucher, 31, broke Australian Ian Healy's long-standing world record of 395 test dismissals against Pakistan in October but lost the record last month when Gilchrist overtook him during the final test against India in Adelaide. Gilchrist announced during that match that he was immediately retiring from test cricket, opening the way for Boucher to reclaim the record. Boucher told reporters he planned to play for another seven to eight years. "It probably would be quite a difficult record to break. I have got time on my side and the longer you play, the more records you will break," he sai
